column1: my own perspective on the same topic:

column5: and baggage. our despair doesn‚Äôt make us weak

column1: 6173;instagram;2019-02-28 05:06:46;FALSE;"celebrating the countdown to the online release march 5th of the don't silence me music video with this beautiful portrait series shot by @katie_nolan_photography. this is me. my mouth taped. no words as sometimes it's hard to put into words what it is that's holding you down. that's weighing heavily on you. until last year when i started to look at the ramifications of the sexual assualt that happened to me at the beginning of my career by a film director in france i had no idea how much my life had been derailed by that event. how much fear i was retaining and operating from. i didn't know what i didn't know. until bit by bit through so much yoga
column3: books and faith i started to shine a light onto the cobwebs which were obscuring my heart and finally to heal. so this blank tape is for all that isn't obvious. for all the words that you aren't even conscious of curtailing your strength and potential. here's to shining a bright neon light onto things and stepping out into the sunshine. .

column1: 6180;instagram;2019-02-28 05:09:09;FALSE;"celebrating the countdown to the online release march 5th of the don't silence me music video with this beautiful portrait series shot by @katie_nolan_photography. this is me. my mouth taped. no words as sometimes it's hard to put into words what it is that's holding you down. that's weighing heavily on you. until last year when i started to look at the ramifications of the sexual assualt that happened to me at the beginning of my career by a film director in france i had no idea how much my life had been derailed by that event. how much fear i was retaining and operating from. i didn't know what i didn't know. until bit by bit through so much yoga
column3: books and faith i started to shine a light onto the cobwebs which were obscuring my heart and finally to heal. so this blank tape is for all that isn't obvious. for all the words that you aren't even conscious of curtailing your strength and potential. here's to shining a bright neon light onto things and stepping out into the sunshine. .

column3: not destroying each other with anger

column2: i‚Äôm yi. for my day job i work in customer service at an insurance company and over the years i have dabbled in a few different things in my hope to be a modern day renaissance woman. you could say my driving force is the pursuit of knowledge. i was accepted into uc berkeley after high school but found it very difficult to find the motivation to attend classes or do the coursework. consequently
column3: i was dismissed from the school and i put getting my degree on hold for a few years. after my experience i found a renewed sense of purpose and i finally went back to finish the classes i needed and in 2012 obtain my ba in anthropology. in the years following that
column4: i have learned the value of understanding myself and having the courage to accept and to love who i am. i love to explore the outdoors and to travel as much of the world as i can. i have been fortunate enough to experience rappelling 165 feet down into the moaning caverns of california
column6: feed the monkeys of mt. arashiyama

column1: 6366;instagram;2019-02-28 01:18:47;FALSE;"rebuilding me: day one. one day you will wake up and you will perceive the world in a much simpler light. you will become aware of the significance of your happiness; you will realise that your freedom is within your grasp; you will let go of the frivolous responsibilities that bind you to stress
column2: anxiety and the inability to progress. the day before
column3: you would‚Äôve been in limbo; you would‚Äôve been questioning your choices and your purpose and your future; and you would‚Äôve been existing in a bleak and hopeless reality - but
column5: your reality will be a stranger to yesterday‚Äôs reality. you will open your eyes for the first time this morning
column6: but also for the first time in a long time. your day one will feel as freeing and as promising as mine. on our day one
column7: we will focus on moving forward: away from the pain and the anguish. we will move upwards from something we thought we could never escape
column8: yet we can. your day of complete turnaround will come because the mind can only suffer finitely; then it will adapt in order to keep the body alive. look forward to this moment... it feels good. ~copingdiary ~

column1: 6669;instagram;2019-02-27 20:26:38;FALSE;"after seeing so many professionals i realized they just don't seem to understand. i had one psychiatrist tell me that i couldn't travel the world in a coffin. i faked a smile so she'd move on.
everyone's told me i have all these dreams like traveling the world so that means i have a reason to live right!? that's great! right?
except what is it telling to you
column2: that i do have all these dreams. like visiting china and finland and canada. and learning asl and how to animate and to dance and martial arts. and yet i reached a point i was willing to let all that go just to escape the pain. why doesn't that speak to you?

column1: everyone ignores that part and acts as though i'm better because i survived. i'm not. i'm trying my best but most of the time i'm not doing it for myself. and i lose everything else that helps me hold on.
i just wish that more people understood that just because a suicide attempt failed doesn't mean the person is healed and has a new zest for life now. that's not how this works.

i wrote a blog titled ""a #metoo guide for outdoorsy dudes"". to be honest
column4: i didn't edit it particularly well
column5: and didn't think much about it after it published. but it was also the culmination of a decade in the outdoor industry
column6: a year watching #metoo be talked about everywhere but outside
column7: and a long-winded text vent conversation with a good friend.

column1: the blog went about as close as i've ever gotten to ""viral""
column2: getting accessed over 60k times and bringing in comments and traffic from all over the country. the internet is a mysterious
column3: mysterious place i tell you. at the time
column5: ""wait - i think i should somehow be leveraging this to make some money or contacts?!"" ... but was also working as a director

column3: the piece did connect me with the great folks at the university of nebraska - lincoln. on friday
column4: i'll be speaking about the topic of the blog post at their flatland climbing festival. i'm proud (and a bit nervous!) to join the company of past speakers like brendan leonard and jeremy collins and looking forward to spending time on a university campus again.

column1: i hope that if there are any nebraskans out there (say hello in the comments!) that you'll join. and if any of you past or present cornhuskers have any must-sees or eats in lincoln

column1: 6817;instagram;2019-02-27 18:45:00;FALSE;"it is national eating disorder awareness (neda) week
column2: so i wanted to share with you the connection between eating disorders and sexual assault. .

column1: many challenges that survivors face may place them at greater risk for developing an eating disorder.
